# Build artifacts and runtime fuzzing state. Curated seeds live under seeds/ and
# ARE committed; the evolving corpus and crash artifacts are generated locally.
#
# Cargo.lock IS committed (this is a binary crate, not a published library): the
# fuzz crate resolves independently of the workspace, so without a lockfile CI
# re-resolves every run and can drift onto transitive versions that don't build
# (e.g. curve25519-dalek 5.0.0-rc.1 pulling an ff that tari_bulletproofs_plus
# can't compile against). Committing the lock makes the fuzz build reproducible.
target/
corpus/
artifacts/
coverage/
